4572ac82a3ecd9381ccdb0ec103166ccc794197e35ccc8eec69088e7f17","size_bytes":4294,"source_description":"Center for Strategic and International Studies commentary by Ryan C. Berg, Mark F. Cancian, Joseph S. Bermudez Jr., Jennifer Jun, Henry Ziemer, and Chris H. Park, published January 9, 2026; captured as relevant text extract during defendant merits investigation.","source_url":"https://www.csis.org/analysis/imagery-venezuela-shows-surgical-strike-not-shock-and-awe","storage_name":"38/383c84572ac82a3ecd9381ccdb0ec103166ccc794197e35ccc8eec69088e7f17","submitted_by_role":"defendant","submitted_phase":"arguments","text_readable":true,"title":"CSIS imagery analysis: surgical strike, not shock and awe"},{"admissibility_status":"submitted_evidence","created_at":"2026-06-30T00:42:13Z","evidence_id":"ev_7d30fcd0d9f7_submitted-evidence-02-plaintiff-7d30fcd0d9f7","mime_type":"text/plain","original_name":"submitted-evidence-02-plaintiff-7d30fcd0d9f7.txt","record_visibility":"juror_visible","relevance":"Independent timeline corroborating December 2025 blockade/covert strike context and January 3, 2026 large-scale U.S. strike across Caracas, capture of Maduro and Flores, and removal from Venezuela.","retrieval_timestamp":"2026-06-30T00:45:00Z","sha256":"7d30fcd0d9f704222f94166d25b9a1221e206e971b247a0beb4c9cee7ba25372","size_bytes":3389,"source_description":"PBS NewsHour page carrying Associated Press timeline by Regina Garcia Cano and AP contributors, captured as relevant text extract during plaintiff merits investigation.","source_url":"https://www.pbs.org/newshour/world/a-timeline-of-u-s-military-escalation-against-venezuela-leading-to-maduros-capture","storage_name":"7d/7d30fcd0d9f704222f94166d25b9a1221e206e971b247a0beb4c9cee7ba25372","submitted_by_role":"plaintiff","submitted_phase":"arguments","text_readable":true,"title":"PBS/AP timeline of U.S. escalation leading to Maduro capture"},{"admissibility_status":"submitted_evidence","created_at":"2026-06-30T00:41:48Z","evidence_id":"ev_e0e0fb921ec9_submitted-evidence-01-plaintiff-e0e0fb921ec9","mime_type":"text/plain","original_name":"submitted-evidence-01-plaintiff-e0e0fb921ec9.txt","record_visibility":"juror_visible","relevance":"Official U.S. source describing the January 3, 2026 military operation in Caracas, Venezuela, including location, military character, planning, special operations forces, ground extraction force, and aircraft support.","retrieval_timestamp":"2026-06-30T00:44:00Z","sha256":"e0e0fb921ec90639876fb9c4c5697b4f6e3a0fd6a37b4b6befc970412f1f4687","size_bytes":3556,"source_description":"U.S. Department of War / Pentagon News article by Matthew Olay, published January 3, 2026, captured as relevant text extract during AAR plaintiff merits investigation.","source_url":"https://www.war.gov/News/News-Stories/Article/Article/4370431/trump-announces-us-militarys-capture-of-maduro/","storage_name":"e0/e0e0fb921ec90639876fb9c4c5697b4f6e3a0fd6a37b4b6befc970412f1f4687","submitted_by_role":"plaintiff","submitted_phase":"arguments","text_readable":true,"title":"Official U.S. Department of War account of Operation Absolute Resolve in Caracas"}]},"turn":{"attempts_max":3,"attempts_remaining":3,"completed":false,"deadline":"2026-06-30T01:09:05.664729479Z","deliberation_round":3,"member_id":"C3","opportunity_id":"deliberation:3:C3","phase":"deliberation","remaining_ms":894970,"role_id":"council","turn_number":18}},"isError":false},"server":"aar","tool":"list_evidence"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782780850694},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to decide vote. Review evidence: Plaintiff's three evidence items establish US military operation in Caracas, with large force, aiming to capture Maduro. Defendant's CSIS says operation was narrow, law enforcement, not intended to establish territorial control. The proposition: \"The United States invaded Venezuela between Nov 3, 2025 and Jan 31, 2026... commenced a military offensive intended to establish control over any portion of Venezuela.\" Need to assess if record shows intent to establish control over any portion. Evidence does not explicitly state intent to control territory; only that they captured target and used control of corridor. So under preponderance, it's more likely not intended to establish control over territory, but a raid. Thus vote not_demonstrated.\n\nProvide concise rationale ≤3 sentences. Then call submit_council_vote.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-85b091f789e0c782","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"not_demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted evidence confirms U.S. military force in Caracas and a capture operation, but no source demonstrates an intent to establish control over Venezuelan territory; the record characterizes the mission as a narrow, law‑enforcement raid rather than an offensive aimed at territorial control.\"}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openai/gpt-oss-120b","usage":{"input":13989,"output":263,"cacheRead":2048,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16300,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782780850695,"responseId":"gen-1782780850-Eyk08Kjf0xA99TfQE5pH"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-85b091f789e0c782","toolName":"mcp","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C3\ncase_id: arb-ex05-20260630003505\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:3:C3\nremaining_ms: 891063\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex05-20260630003505\",\"member_id\":\"C3\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-30T01:09:05.664729479Z\",\"deliberation_round\":3,\"member_id\":\"C3\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:3:C3\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":891063,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":